me\">PING RESPONSE</span>\n        <div class=\"status-bar\">\n          <div class=\"status-progress\"></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {\n      const pingValue = document.querySelector('.adapted-value');\n      const progressBar = document.querySelector('.status-progress');\n      \n      function simulatePing() {\n        const randomPing = Math.floor(Math.random() * 150) + 10;\n        pingValue.textContent = randomPing + ' ms';\n        \n        pingValue.className = 'adapted-value';\n        if(randomPing < 50) {\n          pingValue.classList.add('ping-low');\n          progressBar.style.width = '30%';\n        } else if(randomPing < 100) {\n          pingValue.classList.add('ping-medium');\n          progressBar.style.width = '60%';\n        } else {\n          pingValue.classList.add('ping-high');\n          progressBar.style.width = '90%';\n        }\n      }\n      \n      setInterval(simulatePing, 3000);\n      simulatePing();\n    });\n  </script>\n</body>\n\n</html>",
